💰 ReimburseIQ — Reimbursement Management System
A full-stack web application for managing employee expense reimbursements with multi-level approval workflows, AI-powered receipt scanning, and real-time currency conversion.
📁 Project Structure
reimbursement-app/
├── backend/
│   ├── app.js                  ← Express server entry point
│   ├── package.json
│   ├── requirements.txt        ← Node.js dependency list
│   ├── .env.example            ← Copy to .env and fill in values
│   ├── routes/
│   │   ├── auth.js             ← Signup / Login / Me
│   │   ├── users.js            ← Team management (admin)
│   │   ├── expenses.js         ← Submit & list expenses
│   │   ├── approvals.js        ← Approve / Reject / Override
│   │   ├── company.js          ← Company info & approval flows
│   │   ├── ocr.js              ← AI receipt scanning (Claude Vision)
│   │   └── currency.js         ← Exchange rates & conversion
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   └── auth.js             ← JWT authentication middleware
│   └── utils/
│       ├── dataStore.js        ← JSON file-based data store
│       └── currency.js         ← Currency conversion helper
├── frontend/
│   ├── index.html              ← Single-page app entry point
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css           ← All styles
│   └── js/
│       ├── api.js              ← Backend API client
│       ├── auth.js             ← Login / Signup logic
│       ├── expenses.js         ← Expense forms & tables
│       ├── approvals.js        ← Approval actions
│       ├── users.js            ← Team management UI
│       ├── flows.js            ← Approval flow builder UI
│       ├── ui.js               ← Shared UI helpers (toasts, modals, OCR)
│       └── app.js              ← App init, routing, navigation
└── data/                       ← Auto-created JSON data files
    ├── companies.json
    ├── users.json
    ├── expenses.json
    └── flows.json
🚀 Setup & Installation
1. Clone / Download the project
cd reimbursement-app/backend
2. Install dependencies
npm install
3. Configure environment variables
cp .env.example .env
Edit .env and fill in:
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
JWT_SECRET=your_long_random_secret_here
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here       # For AI receipt scanning
EXCHANGE_RATE_API_KEY=your_key_here           # Optional, free tier works
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5000
DATA_DIR=./data
4. Start the server
# Development (with auto-reload)
npm run dev

# Production
npm start
5. Open the app
Visit http://localhost:5000 in your browser.
🔑 Getting API Keys
Anthropic API Key (for OCR receipt scanning)
Go to https://console.anthropic.com
Create an account and generate an API key
Add it to .env as ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
Exchange Rate API (for currency conversion)
Go to https://www.exchangerate-api.com
Sign up for free (1,500 requests/month free)
Add key to .env as EXCHANGE_RATE_API_KEY
The app also works without this key (uses fallback rates)
