🔗 API Endpoints
Auth
POST /api/auth/signup     Create company + admin
POST /api/auth/login      Login
GET  /api/auth/me         Get current user
Expenses
GET  /api/expenses                 List (role-filtered)
GET  /api/expenses/pending-mine    Pending for current approver
GET  /api/expenses/:id             Get single expense
POST /api/expenses                 Submit new expense
DELETE /api/expenses/:id           Delete (admin only)
Approvals
POST /api/approvals/:id/action     Approve or reject
POST /api/approvals/:id/override   Admin override
GET  /api/approvals/stats          Dashboard stats
Users
GET    /api/users          List company users
POST   /api/users          Create user (admin)
PUT    /api/users/:id      Update role/manager
DELETE /api/users/:id      Delete user (admin)
GET    /api/users/managers List managers
Company & Flows
GET  /api/company          Get company info
PUT  /api/company          Update company name
GET  /api/company/flow     Get approval flow
POST /api/company/flow     Save approval flow
GET  /api/company/stats    Dashboard analytics
OCR
POST /api/ocr/scan          Multipart image upload
POST /api/ocr/scan-base64   Base64 image (used by frontend)
Currency
GET  /api/currency/countries        List all countries + currencies
GET  /api/currency/rates/:base      Exchange rates for base currency
POST /api/currency/convert          Convert amount between currencies
✨ Features
Authentication: JWT-based login. First signup auto-creates a company and admin account.
Multi-currency: Submit expenses in any currency. Managers see amounts in company's base currency.
Multi-level approval: Configure sequential steps (Manager → Finance → Director).
Conditional rules: Sequential / Percentage / Specific approver / Hybrid.
AI OCR: Upload receipt photo → Claude Vision extracts amount, date, merchant, category automatically.
Role-based access: Employee, Manager, Admin with different permissions.
Data persistence: JSON file store (no DB required). Replace utils/dataStore.js for MongoDB/PostgreSQL.
🔧 Deploying to Render
Push project to GitHub
Create a new Web Service on Render
Set Root Directory to backend
Set Build Command: npm install
Set Start Command: node app.js
Add all environment variables from .env
Done — Render will serve both API and frontend from the same process
📝 Notes
Data is stored as JSON files in the data/ directory. For production, swap utils/dataStore.js with a real database adapter (MongoDB with Mongoose, or PostgreSQL with Prisma).
The frontend is served as static files from Express — no separate deployment needed.
OCR works without ANTHROPIC_API_KEY but will return an error asking the user to fill manually.
